Media Description:
Hello Everyone!

I'm thrilled to share my recent experience at the Gear Up Season 2 hackathon, a gateway event for the Smart India Hackathon 2023, hosted by Lovely Professional University.

Over the course of 36 intense hours, my team and I successfully developed and deployes a fully dynamic website complete with a sequential chatbot. Additionally, we deployed an NLP model using a decision tree algorithm tailored to our specific problem statement. Gathering relevant data proved to be a challenge, but we overcame it by creating our own dataset from matching books and utilizing web scraping techniques to extract information from upto 100 web pages.

This hackathon was a thrilling roller coaster ride, filled with valuable lessons and challenges that pushed our boundaries. I'm grateful for the opportunity to learn, build, and collaborate closely with my talented teammates.

I want to extend my appreciation to my incredible teammates: LANKADASU NAGA VENKATA YASWANTH, Jaswanth Singh Kumar Lankadasu, Pranav Rangavajhula, Satya Reddy, and Navya Ramani. We made a fantastic team, and I'm eagerly looking forward to future collaborations with you all! ?

Hey everyone! ?

I'm thrilled to share the news that I've secured my passes for the much-anticipated Generative AI 3-hour mega workshop hosted by the visionary CEO of NxtWave, Rahul Attuluri! ? #MyAIAvatar

During this workshop, I'm eager to delve into a wide range of cutting-edge topics and technologies that are shaping the future of AI: ??

Large Language Models: These powerful AI systems utilize deep learning to comprehend and generate human language, opening up a world of possibilities. ??

Gradio: Excitingly, we'll explore how to create AI apps with minimal coding using Gradio, simplifying the development process. ??

Vector Databases: Managing high-dimensional unstructured data and identifying similar vectors with limitless scalability will be a game-changer. ???

Hugging Face: This platform empowers us to build, train, and deploy ML models, providing access to state-of-the-art NLP models. ??

OpenAI APIs: I can't wait to learn how these #apis help developers integrate NLP, text generation, and other language-based functionalities into their applications seamlessly. ??

Google Colab: With no hardware limitations, #google Colab allows us to write, execute, and share code effortlessly, making the development journey smoother. ??

LangChain: This innovative #framework enables the combination of Large Language Models with external computation and data sources. With LangChain, we can build chatbots, answer questions, summarize text, generate code, analyze data, and so much more! ??

I'm sincerely grateful to the #nxtwaveteam and Rahul sir for organizing such an exciting and knowledge-packed session. Looking forward to expanding my horizons in the world of AI and building my very own AI Avatar! ?? #aiworkshop  #techinnovation  #futureofai #nxtwave #openai  

Let's #connect on #linkedin and share our #thoughts on this remarkable #session! See you there! ??

Today I have completed the Promptbase challenge by NxtWave

The main objective of the challenge is to get a detailed overview of prompts, prompt engineering, and upload the 5 best pictures of the generated pictures with their prompt and seed values

The main things I have learned during the challenge are...
->What AI art and stable diffusion are...
->I have studied and experimented with various AI art models such as :
    Dreamstudio
    DALL.E 2
    Google collaboratory workspace
    Midjourney

->During this process, I have got to know how to input prompts for different AI models and different ways to study an AI model

The thing is none of these pictures exists in the real world, and the places, persons and objects generated by the model are completely generated by the AI model itself!!!
